\u2019s collection <img alt=\"\" class=\"lazyload\" data-src=\"\" src=\"/media/images/25-PK-20190716-0500-PK-Tamil_Nadus_seaweed_ha.width-1440.jpg\" style=\" height:auto;\"/> PHOTO \u2022 M. Palani Kumar Preparing to dry the seaweed <img alt=\"\" class=\"lazyload\" data-src=\"\" src=\"/media/images/26-PK-20190716-0215-PK-Tamil_Nadus_seaweed_ha.width-1440.jpg\" style=\" height:auto;\"/> PHOTO \u2022 M. Palani Kumar Others carrying their collection amid a carpet of seaweed spread out to dry <img alt=\"\" class=\"lazyload\" data-src=\"\" src=\"/media/images/27-PK-20190716-0581-PK-Tamil_Nadus_seaweed_ha.width-1440.jpg\" style=\" height:auto;\"/> PHOTO \u2022 M. Palani Kumar And then it\u2019s back to their homes on land, after hours at the sea and under water Cover photo: A. Mookupori pulling the net bag. Now 35, she h as been diving for seaweed since she was eight years old. (Photo: M. Palani Kumar/PARI) Many thanks to Senthalir S. for her generous help with this story . PARI\u2019s nationwide reporting project on climate change is part of a UNDP-supported initiative to capture that phenomenon through the voices and lived experience of ordinary people. Want to republish this article?", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "394565ce-a3ca-489c-ab48-2178ade2fbd6": {"__data__": {"id_": "394565ce-a3ca-489c-ab48-2178ade2fbd6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://ruralindiaonline.org/en/articles/tamil-nadus-seaweed-harvesters-in-rough-seas/", "Author": "\n\n\n\nReporter :\n\n\n\nM. Palani Kumar\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n", "Publisher": "People's Archive of Rural India", "Type": "Web"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Tamil Nadu\u2019s seaweed harvesters in rough seas", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://ruralindiaonline.org/en/articles